As for the students'resumption of classes, Bai Yansong was interviewed yesterday (March 13) by Wang Dengfeng, director of the Office of the Leading Group of the Ministry of Education's work to deal with the epidemic. Wang responded to questions about whether priority should be given to returning to school in the third year of high school and the Third Year of junior high school, and when universities will open.

In the case of ensuring security, priority junior high school students resume school

Wang Dengfeng, director of the Office of the Leading Group of the Ministry of Education's response to the new pneumonia epidemic, said: the Ministry of Education has clearly stated in several circulars that under the premise of ensuring safety, students should first start their senior year and junior year of high school. Because they are graduating classes, senior three students need to review the college entrance examination, junior three students need to take the high school entrance examination, these students need to go back to school as soon as possible.

The opening of the university involves inter-provincial mobility, the time will continue to be delayed

Wang Dengfeng, director of the Office of the Ministry of Education's Leading Group on the response to the new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic, said: the opening of a university is just like the opening of a primary or middle school. We follow the same principles. There is only one big difference: The opening of university students, involving a considerable number of inter-provincial students. There are now more than 40 million university students in our country, more than 10 million of them will move across provinces, and another 30 million will move within provinces.

From this figure, if you add primary and secondary schools, the whole school opening is more than three hundred million people in the country-wide mobility. Therefore, it is a very difficult task with the widest range of mobility, the highest degree of aggregation, and the biggest social impact. In this process, we first have to solve the problem of the opening of primary and secondary schools in the vicinity. If primary and secondary schools basically open or if the epidemic situation is further controlled, then we will consider the opening of universities. So, it's clear that college starts relatively late.
